creator: Nectar Technologies Inc
descriptionHtml:
Make data-driven decisions within your commercial beekeeping operation by tracking each colony over its entire lifetime.

The Nectar app is designed for the migratory apiary worker who doesn't have time to spare. To complete a yard report, select the actions and observations from your yard visit and assign them to the colonies in that yard from the comfort of your pickup. If you want to report on specific hives, select the actions or observations that are relevant to those colonies, and quickly tap your smartphone on the RFID tags associated with those colonies.

Keep colony records on:

- Location
- Mortality
- Deadout
- Queen line
- Feed
- Treatment
- And so much more!

Access your data on a browser through Nectar Manager in order to make sense of your records. Become a more data-driven commercial beekeeper and dive into:

- Location's effect on your winter mortality
- The queen line best suited for your objectives
- The varroa treatment strategy best suited to your context
- Or anything else you need to raise healthy and productive bees!

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
As your teams are moving in and out of orchards, we were busy fixing bugs. Namely :
* The yard maps not showing on some phones ;
* Inspection reports made offline being lost after killing the app ;
* The app refreshing when switched to landscape mode ;
* The app not automatically using the phone's default language ;
* And a bug preventing beekeepers to move hives in some cases.
Last but not least, we have updated the audio feedback when a scanning error occurs.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
This update offers beekeepers improved visibility into data collected during previous yard visits to help make more informed decisions.
- Historic data: For each yard and hive, access information from previous visits.
- Scan a hive : From the homepage, scan 1 hive to access historic data.
- Yard search: From the homepage, access any yard page.
- Track hives: Confirm or change the yard you are assigning hives to.
And more.
